channel.title: [PI] Cannot attack corp beast & Tormented demons
channel.description:
Hey i downloaded hybrid pvp v3 source, its a great source and all but im wondering how do i fix corp beast and tormented demons? i went to attack them but nothing happens :S im wondering if this is a server side or a client side issue? but whatever it is im not sure how to fix :S Im hoping someone does? :)
Thanks for reading
~HydraVision~

item.title: [PI] Cannot attack corp beast & Tormented demons
item.dc:creator: @Extortion Extortion
item.description:
@Extortion wrote:

Fixed it finally. Well tormented was easy just go into your npc.cfg and fix the hp. Then corp i had to look up the id for it. I found that it wasnt even the right one. the one i used was 8133 and then i compiled tested worked great. Thanks this thread helped a lot.

item.dc:creator: @hydravision hydravision
item.description:
@hydravision wrote:

[quote=“yo dude 1345, post:13, topic:391902”]Code: [Select] case 6451: if (c.absX == 3304 && c.absY == 9375) { c.getPA().movePlayer(3305, 9375, 4); c.sendMessage(“Prepare for the strongest monster in the game!”); c.sendMessage(“Note: It has 3 waves on it’s hp bar!”); } else { c.autoRet = 0; c.getCombat().resetPlayerAttack(); c.getPA().movePlayer(3304, 9375, 0); }

item.title: [PI] Cannot attack corp beast & Tormented demons
item.dc:creator: @hydravision hydravision
item.description:
@hydravision wrote:

Yer all that is fine, I fixed tormented demons cos in npc.cfg there was 0 hp set so i set a hp amount from my old source and that seemed to fix them

But i also noticed i did a

::npc 8133 (corp beast id)
I did that at a random place, he spawned perfectly and i could attack him then
It seems to be when i teleport in through the gates to get to him it bugs him and u cant attack or somthing So im thinking ill remove his spawn and re-spawn him some where else unless you know how to fix here the code for the teleporting through the gate

case 6451: if (c.absX == 3304 && c.absY == 9375) { c.getPA().movePlayer(3305, 9375, 4); c.sendMessage("Prepare for the strongest monster in the game!"); c.sendMessage("Note: It has 3 waves on it's hp bar!"); } else { c.autoRet = 0; c.getCombat().resetPlayerAttack(); c.getPA().movePlayer(3304, 9375, 0); }

item.description:
@yo_dude_1345 wrote:

Ok go into your npc.java and search the ids of the tormented demon and corp beast make sure there combat level and hp ammount are set. Also if thats not the case o into your auto-spawn.java and make sure all the requirements for the are filled like the npc id the x and y cordinates the walk ect… like below. EXAMPLE BELOW

// npc spawnX spawnY height walk maxhit attack defence description

spawn = 559 3237 3426 0 0 40 550 295 cbowshop
